  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6751 sitting above the GEX flip (6710) but trapped in a massive negative gamma cluster from 6735-6755, dealers are forced to buy this breakout move higher, adding fuel to the rally. The regime is BREAKOUT with heavy negative GEX concentration right at current levels, meaning any directional move will be amplified as dealers chase - upside acceleration likely targets the 6800 positive gamma wall where dealer selling pressure kicks in. Watch 6745 (-9950M) as the key amplification level and 6800 as the natural resistance zone where hedging flows reverse.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile grinding higher toward 6800 with dealers buying the breakout.",
